HEADWORD: Celebrated
<hw>Cel"e*bra`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
celebrity; distinguished; renowned.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Celebrated</qex> for the politeness of his manners.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Distinguished; famous; noted; famed; renowned;
illustrious. See <er>Distinguished</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Celebration</ent>⟦br⟧
